# Frontend env vars
#
# As of 2026-05-20, the frontend NO LONGER requires VITE_SUPABASE_*
# env vars at build time. Supabase URL + anon key are fetched at
# runtime from the backend's /api/config endpoint (which reads them
# from SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in Railway env vars).
#
# This means you can run `npm run build:safe` in any environment
# without any local env vars and the resulting bundle will work in
# production. The build-safe guard now verifies the OPPOSITE — that
# no Supabase JWT was accidentally re-inlined into the bundle.
#
# For local development against a local backend, no frontend env
# vars are needed. Just make sure your local backend has SUPABASE_URL
# and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY set (see top-level .env.example).

# (intentionally empty — runtime config fetch handles this now)
